  29:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/util/Memory.h **** // This leaves the question how to detect 64-bit. According to this document,
  30:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/util/Memory.h **** //   http://gcc.fyxm.net/summit/2003/Porting%20to%2064%20bit.pdf
  31:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/util/Memory.h **** // page 114, "[The] LP64 model [...] is used by all 64-bit UNIX ports" so it's indeed
  32:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/util/Memory.h **** // quite safe, at least within the context of glibc, to equate 64-bit with LP64.
