  27:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h **** /** \internal \class global_math_functions_filtering_base
  28:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  *
  29:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * What it does:
  30:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * Defines a typedef 'type' as follows:
  31:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * - if type T has a member typedef Eigen_BaseClassForSpecializationOfGlobalMathFuncImpl, then
  32:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  *   global_math_functions_filtering_base<T>::type is a typedef for it.
  33:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * - otherwise, global_math_functions_filtering_base<T>::type is a typedef for T.
  34:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  *
  35:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * How it's used:
  36:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * To allow to defined the global math functions (like sin...) in certain cases, like the Array exp
  37:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * When you do sin(array1+array2), the object array1+array2 has a complicated expression type, all 
  38:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * is that it inherits ArrayBase. So we implement a partial specialization of sin_impl for ArrayBas
  39:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * So we must make sure to use sin_impl<ArrayBase<Derived> > and not sin_impl<Derived>, otherwise o
  40:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * specialization won't be used. How does sin know that? That's exactly what global_math_functions_
  41:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * it.
  42:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  *
  43:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * How it's implemented:
  44:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * SFINAE in the style of enable_if. Highly susceptible of breaking compilers. With GCC, it sure do
  45:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  * replace the typename dummy by an integer template parameter, it doesn't work anymore!
  46:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****  */
  47:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h **** 
  48:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h **** template <typename T, typename dummy = void>
  49:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h **** struct global_math_functions_filtering_base {
  50:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h ****   typedef T type;
  51:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h **** };
  52:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h **** 
  53:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h **** template <typename T>
  54:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/MathFunctions.h **** struct always_void {
